{"type":"message","id":"80389f74","parentId":"d430a980","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:49:24.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the commits, I can see that:\n\nToday (2026-04-13):\n- `khuong ninh` — Merge MR → develop (via GitLab MR merge button) ✅ This is fine\n- `Ninh Thanh Khuong` — direct commits to develop (not via MR): \n  - `c0cb23b3` — chore: remove package-lock.json (direct)\n  - `30dec8ff` — fix: resolve lint errors (direct)\n  - `0fdc46e3` — feat: implement background student import (direct)\n  - `eb167e93` — feat: update student... (direct)\n\n\n- `khuong ninh` — Merge MR → develop ✅ OK\n- `Cipher (Agent 03)` — direct commits to develop (on Apr 11)\n\nSo `Ninh Thanh Khuong` is definitely pushing straight to develop without going through merge requests, while `khuong ninh` does use the proper workflow.\n\nLooking back at what the Lead said about \"các agent thôi\" (only agents) - they only wanted the Git Workflow to apply to agents. The real question is whether \"push thẳng lên develop\" refers to direct pushes to the main branch or just bypassing the proper review process. Since the MR merges from develop are technically correct, the issue is more about using the right branch workflow, not the actual merge mechanism.\n\nThe agents are pushing directly to develop without going through feature branches and MRs first, which is what the new Git Workflow is meant to prevent. Let me verify this with the recent commits.","thinkingSignature":"48d8f5a0b3d0ef1c68d42eb2d557fd2dc8891f7f3448cc9def887ceda7134d87"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ihkfuojs4tbs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/81078323/repository/commits?ref_name=develop&per_page=5\" -H \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ncommits = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor c in commits:\n    name = c['author_name']\n    email = c['author_email']\n    agent = '🤖 AGENT' if 'openclaw' in email.lower() or 'agent' in name.lower() else '👤 HUMAN'\n    print(f'{c[\\\"created_at\\\"][:10]} {c[\\\"short_id\\\"]} | {agent} {name} | {c[\\\"title\\\"][:70]}')\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":439,"output":559,"cacheRead":46783,"cacheWrite":379,"totalTokens":48160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776059352635,"responseId":"062bb6d984c121ee175374c4c7ad90a3"}}
