{"type":"message","id":"56492a9a","parentId":"46b626d9","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:01:00.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there's MR !12 on FE (project 81078350) with branch `fix/ci-git-pull-ff-only`. This is the same commit message as MR !9 on BE. The Lead pasted the CI error from the FE pipeline.The issue is: the MR !12's pipeline is `none` (hasn't run or was cancelled), but the direct develop pipeline (2448193908) failed with the git pull error.\n\nThe pipeline 2448193908 is on the `develop` branch itself (not on a merge request). The CI `.gitlab-ci.yml` probably has a job that runs `git pull develop` on every pipeline, and that fails because local develop has diverged from origin develop.\n \nI see the root cause now—the FE `.gitlab-ci.yml` is running `git pull develop` in a job that does a hard reset, but it lacks the `--ff-only` flag, so it can't handle the divergent branches. MR !12 is supposed to fix this by adding that flag to the CI configuration, but that MR itself has no pipeline running yet, likely because the merge hasn't been triggered or the pipeline hasn't started. MR !12's source branch is `fix/ci-git-pull-ff-only`, so the pipeline failure on develop happened because develop had diverged from origin/develop. The commit history shows Orbis's direct push to develop likely caused this divergence, and the `.gitlab-ci.yml` pipeline is running `git pull develop` which fails without `--ff-only`. The fix is to merge MR !12 after confirming the CI changes resolve the issue. I'm checking the MR #9 on the BE side to see if it's still pending or if it's already been addressed.","thinkingSignature":"3a1fee4f3f82727178cf662aa3dd71183e9e14826c8f185778652f1d0ee81ebf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0c1qx48au04y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/81078323/merge_requests/9\" -H \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nmr=json.load(sys.stdin)\np = mr.get('head_pipeline', {})\nprint('BE MR !9:')\nprint('  State:', mr['state'])\nprint('  Branch:', mr['source_branch'], '->', mr['target_branch'])\nprint('  Pipeline:', p.get('status', 'none'))\nprint('  SHA:', mr['sha'])\nprint('  URL:', mr['web_url'])\n\"\necho \"---\"\ncurl -s \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/81078350/merge_requests/12\" -H \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nmr=json.load(sys.stdin)\np = mr.get('head_pipeline', {})\nprint('FE MR !12:')\nprint('  State:', mr['state'])\nprint('  Branch:', mr['source_branch'], '->', mr['target_branch'])\nprint('  Pipeline:', p.get('status', 'none'))\nprint('  SHA:', mr['sha'])\nprint('  URL:', mr['web_url'])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":160,"output":709,"cacheRead":53040,"cacheWrite":825,"totalTokens":54734,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063644060,"responseId":"062bc79de1b0ef2b9ecd2525e17d2a5d"}}
