{"type":"message","id":"161347ad","parentId":"6b8ae4c8","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:57:55.994Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also create a pre-commit hook or git template that sets the author for each agent workspace. Actually, the cleanest solution is to create a `.gitconfig` file per agent workspace that sets the identity.Actually, the best approach is to have each agent set their git config when they start. But since agents run in sessions and may not have persistent git config, let me create a git config file in each workspace.\n\nActually, let me just make sure the global config is set correctly for all agent processes. The agents are spawned as sub-processes of the gateway, so they'll inherit the global git config.Let me also set the git config for the AHV Works projects.","thinkingSignature":"955bae9cea5622e4ce084e2033586f1c70f867c04de569bd1ac5638ceb57e8f4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cg1l17gw57qd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Find all git repos in workspaces and set config\nfind /root/.openclaw/workspaces -name \".git\" -type d 2>/dev/null | while read gitdir; do\n  dir=$(dirname \"$gitdir\")\n  repo=$(basename \"$dir\")\n  git -C \"$dir\" config user.name \"Orbis (master-orchestrator)\" 2>/dev/null\n  git -C \"$dir\" config user.email \"orbis@openclaw.ai\" 2>/dev/null\n  echo \"✅ $repo\"\ndone\n\n# Set global default for any NEW clones\ngit config --global user.name \"Orbis (master-orchestrator)\"\ngit config --global user.email \"orbis@openclaw.ai\"\necho \"✅ Global git config: $(git config --global user.name) <$(git config --global user.email)>\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":144,"output":340,"cacheRead":69660,"cacheWrite":679,"totalTokens":70823,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067063627,"responseId":"062bd4f801080100772e11bde421bbc1"}}
