{"type":"message","id":"9898dc24","parentId":"b7d91d30","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:58:31.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create per-agent git configs. For other agents, I should create a `.gitconfig` file in their workspace that they can source. But since agents are spawned with their own workspace, the simplest approach is to set git config per workspace.\n\nLet me also create a git alias or hook that prepends the agent name to commits. Actually, the cleanest approach for now is to set git config in each agent's workspace directory.\n\nFor the other agents (senior-backend, senior-frontend, etc.), I should set their workspace git config so when they clone and commit, they use their own identity. Let me do that.","thinkingSignature":"9fb752fc62e7c30d3acc77a61a295e9c462c696e3e8e865ea6700f32b96071f4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nq78xuypbe62_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Set git config for each agent workspace (ecosystem infrastructure repos)\nfor ws in senior-backend senior-frontend senior-devops senior-architect senior-qa senior-security planner; do\n  dir=\"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/$ws\"\n  if [ -d \"$dir\" ]; then\n    # Init git if not exists\n    if [ ! -d \"$dir/.git\" ]; then\n      git -C \"$dir\" init --initial-branch=main 2>/dev/null\n    fi\n    git -C \"$dir\" config user.name \"$ws (OpenClaw Agent)\"\n    git -C \"$dir\" config user.email \"$ws@openclaw.ai\"\n    echo \"✅ $ws: $(git -C \"$dir\" config user.name)\"\n  fi\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":185,"output":322,"cacheRead":70053,"cacheWrite":665,"totalTokens":71225,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776067081246,"responseId":"062bd50a1b92fac4e9d21345f2540f1d"}}
