{"type":"message","id":"77e7a867","parentId":"74e1385d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:20:37.197Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw.json doesn't have a default model setting. The model override must be stored per-session in the sessions.json. Looking at the sessions.json, each session entry has a model field. The sessions that use `AHV-Holding-TroLy` suggest that was the model's last selection.\n\nBut where does the agent's default model come from when spawning new sessions? Looking at the grep output - `agent:senior-backend:subagent:e3ca11a2` uses `AHV-Holding-DEV` while others use `TroLy`. This means the agent can use either model. The question is: why does it default to TroLy?\n \nI think I see it now - the agent likely defaults to the first model in models.json unless explicitly overridden. The cleanest fix is to update the models.json to reorder `AHV-Holding-DEV` as the first entry, so new sessions will default to it instead of TroLy.","thinkingSignature":"74aa4ed0b43b858c325a696a57128ec9c9423a0cba3d7a9caca40ad96943dd84"},{"type":"text","text":"Found nguyên nhân. Agent `senior-backend` default model là `AHV-Holding-TroLy` (model đầu tiên trong list). Orbis đổi thứ tự để `AHV-Holding-DEV` thành default:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vtfjo3v7zee5_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/agents/senior-backend/agent/models.json","edits":[{"oldText":"        {\n          \"id\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n          \"name\": \"AHV Holding TroLy\",\n          \"reasoning\": true,\n          \"input\": [\n            \"text\",\n            \"image\"\n          ],\n          \"contextWindow\": 200000,\n          \"maxTokens\": 65536\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"name\": \"AHV Holding DEV\",\n          \"reasoning\": true,\n          \"input\": [\n            \"text\",\n            \"image\"\n          ],\n          \"contextWindow\": 200000,\n          \