{"type":"message","id":"35434cc6","parentId":"a9629ee3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:39:15.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backend is cloned but:\n1. No repositories folder (maybe different structure)\n2. dist/ exists with compiled files — build has passed!\n3. BE server not running\n\nThe subagent got the build to pass. Now it just needs to start the server and test auth endpoints. Let me spawn a quick subagent just for the testing part with a shorter task.","thinkingSignature":"2df4293835a61aac36a3ce03823b1b32cd500618c792143e3859cfa231c48a77"},{"type":"text","text":"Build đã pass ✅ (thư mục `dist/` có file compiled). Subagent cần:\n1. Start BE server (port 5555)\n2. Test auth endpoints\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_na07zevxnp48_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"Start ahv-dtlx-backend and test auth API.\n\n## Context\nBackend already built (dist/ folder exists). Repo at /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/\n\n## Steps\n1. cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend\n2. Start server: yarn start OR node dist/src/app.js (check package.json for correct start command)\n3. Wait for server to be ready (~5s)\n4. Test these endpoints with curl:\n   - POST /api/v1/auth/register (create test user)\n   - POST /api/v1/auth/login (login with test user)\n   - GET /api/v1/auth/profile (get profile with token)\n5. Report results\n\nUse exec tool for all commands. Use exec background=true for the server start, then curl to test.\n\nIf server fails to start, check error logs and try to fix. If MongoDB connection fails, that's ok - report what you found.","label":"DTLX BE Start & Test","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"master-orchestrator","model":"ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV","mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":140,"output":426,"cacheRead":141388,"cacheWrite":401,"totalTokens":142355,"cos