{"type":"message","id":"e4813d03","parentId":"3f053409","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:43:09.128Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron sessions are stale and reporting wrong data. The `e7885813` cron is reading old session IDs from the parent session's `childSessions` list and reporting them as \"active\". But those subagent sessions are actually dead/timed out.\n\nThe current actual active sessions are:\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` - Lead direct ✅\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef` - DTLX 5p progress ✅  \n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d` - Old QLHV 5p cron (stale, should be killed)\n\n\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813` - Agent Status cron (stale, reporting wrong data)\n\nThe real issue is that those cron sessions are running with stale context from when the QLHV group was active, so they're carrying outdated session lists. The DTLX full API test subagent has been stuck for nearly 2 hours and needs to be killed and restarted. I'll clean up the cron sessions and get a fresh subagent running instead.\n\nLooking at the current state: the QLHV cron is reporting incorrect information, the test subagent is blocked because mongosh isn't available in the environment, and most endpoints are returning empty data anyway. The backend is working fine with the JWT fix, so I should just abort this test and provide a summary to the lead about what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"5952417dcade56cce97486709fbfa936c9ede479ef3c810b273f373013ff2b9b"},{"type":"text","text":"Report này **sai hoàn toàn** — cron đọc session ID cũ từ context. Orbis kill cron sai và restart task:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mz8atkitw16z_1","name":"subagents","arguments":{"action":"kill","recentMinutes":999}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1129,"output":389,"cacheRead":56298,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57816,"cost":{