{"type":"message","id":"fc08b70e","parentId":"33e1b54e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:43:42.408Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway timeout. Let me restart the full API test task fresh. The subagent got stuck because mongosh isn't available. Orbis should do this differently - use the BE's existing API to seed data through HTTP calls instead of direct MongoDB access.","thinkingSignature":"a6f107b6e4eec84e3d25469350da2b3d83a3d43741f597cdea9c6a3e0e9288ad"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway timeout. Orbis restart task đúng cách — dùng API để seed thay vì mongosh:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c6ody53j6ayv_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are the DTLX BE API Tester. Test every endpoint and seed data via API calls (NOT mongosh).\n\n## Context\n- Backend: http://localhost:3001 (already running)\n- Login: POST /api/v1/auth/signin with {\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Admin123!\"} → accessToken\n- JWT bug: FIXED ✅ (doc._id)\n- Use AHV-Holding-DEV model\n\n## PHASE 1: Map ALL endpoints\nRead all route files to build complete endpoint list:\n```\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/router.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/routes/v1/education.routes.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/routes/v1/operation.routes.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/routes/v1/notification.routes.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/routes/v1/system.routes.ts\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/modules/*/*.route.ts\n```\nList every endpoint with METHOD and PATH.\n\n## PHASE 2: Seed Data via API\nUse curl or fetch to seed data through HTTP endpoints. Check each module's controller/service for the correct body format:\n\n### Step 2a: Create users (admin should already exist)\n- GET /api/v1/users (to see existing users)\n- Try POST /api/v1/users to create new users\n\n### Step 2b: Create courses\n- POST /api/v1/courses (check validation from courses.validation.ts)\n\n### Step 2c: Create payments (with received_fee field)\n- POST /api/v1/payments\n\n### Step 2d: Create vehicles\n- POST /api/v1/vehicles\n\n### Step 2e: Create stadiums  \n- POST /api/v1/stadiums\n\n### Step 2f: Create internal costs\n- POST /api/v1/internal-costs\n\n### Step 2g: Create students\n- POST /api/v1/student-infos\n\nCheck the validation files first to know required fields.\n\n## PHASE 3: Test ALL endpoints\nFor EACH endpoint:\n1. GET fresh token\n2. Call endpoint\n3. Record: HTTP status, keys in response, data count\n\n## PHASE 4: Test aggregate pipelines\n- GET /api/v1/dashboards/reports/revenues\n- GET /api/v1/dashboards/reports/expenses  \n- GET /api/v1/dashboards/reports/profits (this should work now with data)\n- Any payment aggregation\n\n## Output\nSave detailed report to:\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-14-dtlx-api-test.md\n\nFormat:\n## Module: [name]\n### GET /path - Status: [code]\n- Response keys: [list]\n- Data count: [N]\n- Issues: [none or describe]\n\nBe thorough. Test every single endpoint.","label":"DTLX Full API Test v2","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"master-orchestrator","model":"ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV","runTimeoutSeconds":2400,"mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":241,"output":881,"cacheRead":57325,"cacheWrite":525,"totalTokens":58972,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149002311,"responseId":"062d150b08fbb6fb142d951941ad6934"}}
