{"type":"message","id":"b3fdec7d","parentId":"3368057c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:09:04.487Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `/teacher-infos` endpoint is 404. Let me fix the script and also look at what data we have seeded so far. The key issue is:1. We have 3 courses seeded\n2. Everything else is empty3. We need to seed more data and fix the bugs\n\nLet me first check what endpoints are 404 and fix them. Let me also look at the actual DB to see what we have.\n\nActually, the main issue is that we need to:\n1. Fix the `/teacher-infos` route issue (404)2. Seed more data3. Fix the 500 bugs\n\nLet me check what the `/teacher-infos` 404 is about. Looking at the routes:\n\n\nSo the base `/teacher-infos` GET endpoint isn't mounted in the router, but `/teacher-infos/ranking` is. The education routes show that `teacherRoute` is being used, but it seems like the route file itself doesn't have a base GET handler defined. So the issue is that the `/teacher-infos` route is mounted correctly, but the GET method just isn't defined in the actual route file itself. I need to check the full route structure to understand what's actually missing versus what's being routed to the module.","thinkingSignature":"c7cccc42baa403d7e7a50478cdc05d50f8ddacd23a517827f975f10248708b22"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ffqh6l375yna_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/modules/teacherInfos/teacherInfos.route.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":672,"output":309,"cacheRead":99830,"cacheWrite":1884,"totalTokens":102695,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776150529351,"responseId":"062d1b07034cfa1c33588e1399ed089e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1370207b","parentId":"b3fdec7d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:09:05.078Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ffqh6l375yna_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import express from 'express';\nimport { validate } from 'express-validation';\nimport * as teacherInfosValidation from './teacherInfos.validation';\nimport { teacherInfosController } from './teacherInfos.controller';\n\nconst router = express.Router();\n\nrouter.post(\n    '/',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.createTeacherInfos, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.createTeacherInfos,\n);\n\nrouter.get('/ranking', teacherInfosController.getTeacherRanking);\n\nrouter.get(\n    '/:id',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.getOrDeleteById, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.getTeacherInfosById,\n);\n\nrouter.get(\n    '/user/:userId',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.byUserId, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.getTeacherInfosByUserId,\n);\n\nrouter.patch(\n    '/:id',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.updateTeacherInfosById, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.updateTeacherInfosById,\n);\n\nrouter.delete(\n    '/:id',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.getOrDeleteById, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.deleteTeacherInfosById,\n);\n\nrouter.delete(\n    '/user/:userId',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.byUserId, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.deleteTeacherInfosByUserId,\n);\n\nexport default router;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":53,"aggregated":"import express from 'express';\nimport { validate } from 'express-validation';\nimport * as teacherInfosValidation from './teacherInfos.validation';\nimport { teacherInfosController } from './teacherInfos.controller';\n\nconst router = express.Router();\n\nrouter.post(\n    '/',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.createTeacherInfos, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.createTeacherInfos,\n);\n\nrouter.get('/ranking', teacherInfosController.getTeacherRanking);\n\nrouter.get(\n    '/:id',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.getOrDeleteById, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.getTeacherInfosById,\n);\n\nrouter.get(\n    '/user/:userId',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.byUserId, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.getTeacherInfosByUserId,\n);\n\nrouter.patch(\n    '/:id',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.updateTeacherInfosById, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.updateTeacherInfosById,\n);\n\nrouter.delete(\n    '/:id',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.getOrDeleteById, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.deleteTeacherInfosById,\n);\n\nrouter.delete(\n    '/user/:userId',\n    validate(teacherInfosValidation.byUserId, { context: true }),\n    teacherInfosController.deleteTeacherInfosByUserId,\n);\n\nexport default router;","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776150544795}}
{"type":"message","id":"34791d64","parentId":"1370207b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:09:20.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the `/teacher-infos` route only has:- POST / - GET /ranking\n- GET /:id\n- GET /user/:userId\n- PATCH /:id\n- DELETE /:id\n- DELETE /user/:userId\n\nThere's NO `GET / ` (list all). So the 404 for `GET /teacher-infos` is because there's no such route defined. This is a missing feature - the route file doesn't have a list endpoint.\n\nSame for many other modules. Let me focus on what we need:1. Seed more data to test the pipelines","thinkingSignature":"cd5650f9469aa6fe8de8adbb2b675d2513de54779fb3c320a2b0695510f045b1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2u3ngpqvx594_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check exact validation errors for failed POSTs\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nBASE = \"http://localhost:3001/api/v1\"\n\ndef api(method, path, token=None, data=None):\n    url = f\"{BASE}{path}\"\n    headers = {\"Content-Type\":\"application/json\"}\n    if token: headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"\n    body = json.dumps(data).encode() if data else None\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, data=body, headers=headers, method=method)\n    try:\n        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=20)\n        return resp.status, json.loads(resp.read())\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return e.code, json.loads(e.read().decode()[:500])\n\n_, resp = api(\"POST\", \"/auth/signin\", None, {\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Password123@\"})\ntoken = resp[\"data\"][\"accessToken\"]\n\ntests = [\n    (\"StudentInfos\", \"/student-infos\", {\"username\":\"sv002\",\"password\":\"Password123@\",\"email\":\"sv002@gmail.com\",\"phone\":\"0912345002\",\"identity_card\":\"123456002\"}),\n    (\"LicenseCat\", \"/license-categories\", {\"Name\":\"B2\",\"code\":\"B2\"}),\n    (\"LeadSources\", \"/lead-sources\", {\"Name\":\"Google Ads\"}),\n    (\"LeadInfos\", \"/lead-infos\", {\"Name\":\"Test Lead\",\"phone\":\"0909000001\"}),\n    (\"GuestLead\", \"/guests/leads\", {\"Name\":\"Test\",\"phone\":\"0909000001\"}),\n    (\"IC\", \"/internal-costs\", {\"amount\":500000,\"payment_date\":\"2026-04-05\"}),\n    (\"StudentComment\", \"/student-comments\", {\"comment\":\"Test\"}),\n    (\"ChangePassword\", \"/auth/change-password\", {\"oldPassword\":\"Password123@\",\"newPassword\":\"NewPass123@\"}),\n]\n\nfor name, path, body in tests:\n    s, r = api(\"POST\", path, token, body)\n    err_details = r.get(\"err\",{}).get(\"details\",\"\") if isinstance(r,dict) else \"\"\n    if isinstance(err_details, list):\n        msgs = [e.get(\"message\",\"\") for e in err_details[:2]]\n        print(f\"{s} {name}: {msgs}\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"{s} {name}: {r.get('message','')[:80]}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":393,"output":679,"cacheRead":100884,"cacheWrite":1706,"totalTokens":103662,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776150545097,"responseId":"062d1b1209854c73fdb6da11575deb3d"}}
