{"type":"message","id":"6597efa9","parentId":"3113b12f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:10:56.171Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5g3g2r60rlvm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"getCountNotifiesUnread = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response): Promise<void> => {\n        const userId = String(req.query.user_id);\n        logger.info(`[NotifyUsersController] getCountUnread: Đang đếm tin chưa đọc cho User: ${userId}`);\n\n        const count = await notifyUsersService.getCountNotifiesUnread(userId);\n\n        res.status(httpStatus.OK).json({\n            status: 'success',\n            message: 'Truy vấn số thông báo người dùng chưa đọc thành công!',\n            data: { unreadCount: count },\n        });\n    });"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":102,"aggregated":"getCountNotifiesUnread = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response): Promise<void> => {\n        const userId = String(req.query.user_id);\n        logger.info(`[NotifyUsersController] getCountUnread: Đang đếm tin chưa đọc cho User: ${userId}`);\n\n        const count = await notifyUsersService.getCountNotifiesUnread(userId);\n\n        res.status(httpStatus.OK).json({\n            status: 'success',\n            message: 'Truy vấn số thông báo người dùng chưa đọc thành công!',\n            data: { unreadCount: count },\n        });\n    });","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776150655692}}
{"type":"message","id":"51a06aa5","parentId":"6597efa9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:11:06.887Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The controller reads `req.query.user_id`. If not provided, `userId` would be \"undefined\" string. The service then tries to create `mongoose.Types.ObjectId(\"undefined\")` which fails.\n\nThis is a controller-level bug — the route `/unread/count` should either:\n1. Use `req.user.id` from the JWT (which is the authenticated user)\n2. Require `user_id` as a query param\n\nSince it's under a route that requires auth, it should probably use `req.user.id`. But the controller currently reads from `req.query.user_id`.\n\nLet me check if this is the issue by passing a user_id.","thinkingSignature":"801de9f17d795e8063ee160481229db0b5a780f0384172202ea603a49dbba73c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8zkujtit8y0j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nBASE = \"http://localhost:3001/api/v1\"\ndef api(method, path, token=None, data=None):\n    url = f\"{BASE}{path}\"\n    headers = {\"Content-Type\":\"application/json\"}\n    if token: headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"\n    body = json.dumps(data).encode() if data else None\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, data=body, headers=headers, method=method)\n    try:\n        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=20)\n        return resp.status, json.loads(resp.read())\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return e.code, json.loads(e.read().decode()[:500])\n\n_, resp = api(\"POST\", \"/auth/signin\", None, {\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Password123@\"})\ntoken = resp[\"data\"][\"accessToken\"]\n\n# Test notify-users/unread/count with user_id param\ns, r = api(\"GET\", \"/notify-users/unread/count?user_id=69dde49db5c07c63bb44ba89\", token)\nprint(f\"Notify users with user_id ({s}):\", json.dumps(r, indent=2)[:300])\nPYEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":269,"output":437,"cacheRead":107816,"cacheWrite":427,"totalTokens":108949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776150656212,"responseId":"062d1b825010b2760527e012a268a2ff"}}
