{"type":"message","id":"15c5c8a1","parentId":"d7f07b3d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:11:18.307Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"With `user_id` param, it returns 200! So the bug is that the controller reads from `req.query.user_id` but when not provided, it gets \"undefined\" string → mongoose ObjectId fails.\n\nThe fix should be: use `req.user.id` from JWT when user_id is not provided. Let me fix this in the controller.\n\nNow let me also check the student-infos validation issue. Let me look at the schema to understand what fields are needed.","thinkingSignature":"c9a16440517dab05dc164b5bd5ca1c2701177fd58a14cc55f9990e4d97fb5e9e"},{"type":"text","text":"Bug confirmed — controller dùng `req.query.user_id` nhưng không có default từ JWT. Fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sce8sp1jupws_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/modules/notifyUsers/notifyUsers.controller.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"        const userId = String(req.query.user_id);\n        logger.info(`[NotifyUsersController] getCountUnread: Đang đếm tin chưa đọc cho User: ${userId}`);","newText":"        const userId = req.query.user_id ? String(req.query.user_id) : String(req.user?.id);\n        logger.info(`[NotifyUsersController] getCountUnread: Đang đếm tin chưa đọc cho User: ${userId}`);"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":226,"output":305,"cacheRead":108115,"cacheWrite":729,"totalTokens":109375,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776150669182,"responseId":"062d1b8fd77d68b1209dfbe4416e4316"}}
