{"type":"message","id":"be593a58","parentId":"0035b2d7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:13:40.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the login response includes a very long `data.doc` object and the HTTP 200 response for login itself might be too large. Wait, no - the login itself returns 200 OK but the response body is being truncated somewhere.\n\nActually, the problem might be with the login response parsing. Let me check - the login response has a large doc object (with permissions array etc). Maybe the response is too long and urllib is having trouble reading it all at once.\n\nWait, actually looking more carefully: the error happens at line 11 (the login call). But line 11 is the login call... and it says \"HTTP Error 500: Internal Server Error\". So the login itself is now returning 500!\n \nThe `/reports/profits` endpoint probably triggered some cascade failure, and now the server's returning 500s across the board. I need to check what's actually happening on the backend.","thinkingSignature":"43f04705e80042db4f8dcd6b339f3a4549da4e3dfcb8664dc038aa2c15552305"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m6ypzn2ne0xf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Password123@\"}' 2>/dev/null | head -c 100","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":539,"output":274,"cacheRead":111046,"cacheWrite":2840,"totalTokens":114699,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776150810353,"responseId":"062d1c1bc93d5f87cf7c4227659d76a8"}}
