{"type":"message","id":"9daff625","parentId":"083dc32b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:29:41.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The route is `/:id/total-time` but I was testing with `/:id/total-time` where `:id` was the course_id (not a vehicle_id). The route expects a vehicle ID but I was passing a course ID. The service tries to cast this to ObjectId which fails because a course ID format isn't the same as a vehicle ObjectId. That's a test error, not a code bug.\n\nLet me now check the `/lessons/detail` endpoint. The error was \"Cast to ObjectId failed\" - this means one of the query parameters was an invalid ObjectId. Let me check the lessons route for the detail endpoint.","thinkingSignature":"16f9a2dc787e27458a92752c70cc2c8aa6977c83b196bfbfbc6751c0853d836e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_apqv2gdoeurw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"detail\\|getDetail\\|/lessons\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/modules/lessons/lessons.route.ts 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":132,"output":209,"cacheRead":128779,"cacheWrite":526,"totalTokens":129646,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776151773423,"responseId":"062d1fdf21e206869b9e83545165c0d2"}}
