{"type":"message","id":"2ecc6f5d","parentId":"8204f0c3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:30:00.545Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the route is `/detail-by-date` not `/detail`. So the test I ran was calling the wrong path. But the error came from somewhere... Let me check the error more carefully. \"Cast to ObjectId failed\" - where is this coming from?\n\nActually wait - the test was hitting `/lessons/detail` which doesn't exist, so Express would return a 404. But the error was a 500 \"Cast to ObjectId failed\" - so maybe Express is routing it to a different handler?\n\nNo wait - `router.get('/detail-by-date', ...)` is the route for detail-by-date. The `/lessons/detail` path would not match any route and should return 404. \n\nBut I'm seeing 500 errors instead. Let me trace through the actual route definitions - the base router mounts at `/lessons` with `/detail-by-date` as a specific sub-route, so there might be a catch-all pattern or something else matching before the 404 handler kicks in.\n\nActually, looking at the test output more carefully, `/lessons/detail` returned 500 with a Cast to ObjectId error. That's strange because Express should return 404 for an undefined route. Unless the Express configuration has a catch-all handler that's trying to process something and failing, or maybe the route validation is triggering before the route matching happens.\n\nLet me trace through what happens when a request hits `/lessons/detail` - it won't match any defined route, so Express should pass it to error handlers or return 404 directly. The 500 with Cast to ObjectId suggests something is trying to validate or process the request path as an ObjectId somewhere in the middleware chain. I'm realizing the issue might be with how the routes are nested—the lessons router is mounted at `/lessons` in the main router, so a GET request to `/lessons/detail` should only match if there's an explicit route for it. Since the route is defined as `/detail-by-date` rather than `/detail`, Express should return 404, but something's returning a 500 error instead, which suggests the server might be crashing on certain query parameters or there's another route handler interfering.","thinkingSignature":"27b060eefa47c60c08e4a5c7d4235d3d114c6ac49a08b7b0a9f41b65820ba25b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nj6til3pj33a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep \"node.*dtlx\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}'","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":159,"output":493,"cacheRead":129211,"cacheWrite":338,"totalTokens":130201,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776151782463,"responseId":"062d1fe88775974a6056ce63c8f54594"}}
