{"type":"message","id":"ae2b77d1","parentId":"10aa5929","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:41:51.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This repo doesn't have the DTLX BE codebase - it's pointing to a different GitHub repo. The DTLX BE codebase was probably cloned directly from GitLab. Let me check if there's a .git folder or if it was downloaded as a zip.\n\nActually, looking at the workspace structure - the DTLX BE workspace is at `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend` but the `.git` folder points to a different repo. This might be a self-contained codebase without git (or git was removed). \n\nGiven that the DTLX BE codebase doesn't have a proper git remote for the actual project, I'll just save my fixes locally and report the results to the Lead. \n\nThe user can then commit and push these changes themselves. Let me document what I've accomplished in MEMORY.md so they have a clear record of the work done.","thinkingSignature":"5da8de6d243d8f9594144a61ef504d791a7fec27f591a568c13fa8477e27a69f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3ub5ddpx1h1m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/.git 2>/dev/null && echo \"git exists\" || echo \"no git\"","timeout":3}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":153,"output":259,"cacheRead":79617,"cacheWrite":248,"totalTokens":80277,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776152502711,"responseId":"062d22b81a69c66469f1b0f2f7ea858d"}}
