{"type":"message","id":"76d2836b","parentId":"64da3f41","timestamp":"2026-04-14T07:43:33.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The cron session `ed2d0b5d` is the old 5p progress report cron that was running in the previous ecosystem. It's status=done but the cron was scheduled to repeat. The group session `-5163901258` (QLHV) is also from the previous ecosystem.\n\nCurrent real active sessions:\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` — Lead direct ✅ (this is my current session)\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef` — DTLX 5p progress cron ✅ (running)\n\n\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813` — Agent Status cron ✅ (running)\n\nEverything else is stale. I need to clean up those old cron sessions since they're not relevant to the current ecosystem, and the heartbeat cron that reported the stale data was just an old scheduled cron that sent outdated information to the group.\n\nThe real issue is that this old cron session was reporting old ecosystem data, which is now resolved. The two stale sessions—the group at -5163901258 and the old progress cron at ed2d0b5d—are both done and shouldn't be rescheduled. I should update the heartbeat state to clear this confusion, then give the Lead a clean status update.\n\nNow I'm looking at the actual state: only three sessions are currently active—the main Lead direct session, the DTLX 5-minute cron, and the Agent Status cron. The rest are stale, so I need to clean those up and verify the heartbeat state file is accurate.","thinkingSignature":"a4a782b515c12b5f4743c12b74770e9b717fa02bddb50408b55ba72d9780b474"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_72x2hc0lt106_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":13328,"output":384,"cacheRead":77856,"cach