{"type":"message","id":"72bd5ba7","parentId":"2fecaefe","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:54:35.387Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead is asking why the API test didn't cover all ~250 endpoints and wants a comprehensive report of which APIs can't return data even though the system has data. Let me do a thorough test covering all possible endpoints including those that need specific data/IDs/roles to return results.\n\nLet me think about what I tested vs what I didn't:\n- I tested ~79 endpoints\n- But there are 221 router calls total per the grep earlier\n- Many endpoints need specific data: coursesStudents, exam results, exam schedules, vehicles, lessons, student-infos, payments, etc. that need actual seeded data\n\nLet me do a comprehensive test now - first I need to understand the full route list and test each one, particularly:\n\n\n1. All coursesStudents endpoints (need course_student data)\n2. All lessons endpoints (need lesson data)\n3. All exams/exam-results/exam-schedules endpoints\n4. All student-infos endpoints\n5. All payments endpoints\n6. All vehicles endpoints\n7. All work-calendars endpoints\n8. All exam-registrations endpoints\n9. All student/teacher comments\n10. All teacher-infos endpoints\n11. All notify-users endpoints\n12. All user role-specific endpoints\n13. All CRUD endpoints\n\nLet me get the full list of routes and test them all comprehensively. First, let me check what the server is currently running.","thinkingSignature":"5885bcab93058e161166b2442f3a9004c5cc3c522f9f7264edfd900405a13a00"},{"type":"text","text":"Em test lại đầy đủ ngay. Server đang chạy chứ?\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l9jmdbe2e44i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Password123@\"}' | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('OK' if d.get('status')=='success' el