{"type":"message","id":"729cab05","parentId":"7f7ab8b0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:21:45.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the pipeline data, I can see:\n\n1. **No running pipelines** - the last pipeline was from March 30, 2026 (about 2 weeks ago)\n2. **All recent pipelines are fast** - success pipelines run in ~3 minutes\n3. **No current pipeline running** - no \"running\" status pipelines\n\nThe \"slow runner\" concern might be about:\n1. No new pipelines being triggered since March 30 (2 weeks ago) - this might be the issue\n2. The latest MR !166 (`feature/clean-architecture-migration → refactor/main`) has `merge_status: \"can_be_merged\"` and `detailed_merge_status: \"mergeable\"` - it can be merged\n\n\n3. The last pipeline for MR !166 was a success on March 30\n\nBut I think the user is asking about GitLab's CI runner infrastructure being slow overall, not just this specific project. I should check the CI config to see what runner they're using and whether there's been any recent degradation. Let me also look at QLHV BE since that project might have more active pipelines running.","thinkingSignature":"0211a2113167a9ba3d54649ffc6f038144e3b996ba90675784d51ac86c0fc6ae"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jb1nbblb25ys_1","name":"gitlab__gitlab_get_file","arguments":{"project_id":"77055841","file_path":".gitlab-ci.yml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":3604,"output":279,"cacheRead":137879,"cacheWrite":1559,"totalTokens":143321,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776162089076,"responseId":"062d482aae98ad512638a9eec1e94d8b"}}
