{"type":"message","id":"c282ca60","parentId":"b341b2b8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:21:56.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No `.gitlab-ci.yml` file in the project. That means there are no CI pipelines configured for this project via GitLab CI. The pipelines we see might be from a different CI system or the project uses external CI/CD.\n\nWait - I see \"source: merge_request_event\" and \"source: push\" for the pipelines. These could be from GitHub Actions or another external CI system, since there's no `.gitlab-ci.yml`.\n\nBut wait, the pipelines ARE being listed through the GitLab API. That means GitLab IS tracking them. Maybe there's a pipeline configured via GitLab's CI but the file was removed, or maybe it was moved to a different location.\n\n\nLet me check the other project to see if it has a different CI configuration.","thinkingSignature":"21c0607597ae44d68be510996cf917aee0c604263f9c68440dd21b2b0db7373b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m8ur9xuwdolr_1","name":"gitlab__gitlab_get_project","arguments":{"project_id":"81078323"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":137,"output":185,"cacheRead":139372,"cacheWrite":3844,"totalTokens":143538,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776162108958,"responseId":"062d483e67045ab20aaa4ad9b6e031ea"}}
