{"type":"message","id":"8369c47c","parentId":"87a6fcfc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:22:12.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see from the project settings:\n- `shared_runners_enabled: false` — no shared GitLab runners\n- `group_runners_enabled: true` — group runners are enabled\n- `build_timeout: 3600` — 1 hour timeout\n\nThis means the project uses **group runners** (specific runners for the `ahv-dtlx` group), not the default shared GitLab runners. The runner slowness could be because:\n1. The group runners are busy with other projects\n2. The runner is on a slow machine\n3. Network issues\n\nBut looking at the data again - the LAST pipeline was on 2026-03-30 (2 weeks ago!). And `last_activity_at` for QLHV BE is `2026-04-14T10:13:33.165Z` (today). \n\nSo QLHV BE is active today but the DTLX BE project shows no new pipelines since 2026-03-30 — over two weeks ago. That's the real issue here.\n\nThe DTLX BE pipeline hasn't been triggered by any recent commits or MRs, which suggests either the branch `feature/clean-architecture-migration` hasn't been pushed to since then, or the CI configuration was removed or changed. Let me check what's actually happening with the recent commits.","thinkingSignature":"126c12f91cfbf675c4c0978fe4f6b0b663ae956ea156a047cdd7b08698234e1f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kmb1tqnopdjr_1","name":"gitlab__gitlab_list_commits","arguments":{"project_id":"77055841","ref_name":"feature/clean-architecture-migration","per_page":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1782,"output":335,"cacheRead":142932,"cacheWrite":501,"totalTokens":145550,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776162118177,"responseId":"062d4848c563db4a0149b66b53fb6d29"}}
