{"type":"message","id":"6af6cd66","parentId":"ceff545e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:38:29.843Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat from a cron session. The QLHV group (-5163901258) is mentioned as running again - \"Tuition work, 4 sub-agents spawned\". This was supposed to be stopped. Let me check.\n\nActually, this is from a different cron session (cron:e7885813 is the Agent Status cron, but the tg-group:-5163901258 is a group session that's running \"Tuition work\"). This seems to be from the old ecosystem cron sessions.\n\nThe key question is whether this is actually a live session or stale data from old crons. The session age of \"13m\" is suspicious since those old cron sessions should have reported stale data.\n\n\nLooking at the group session key, it's still marked as running in the system, which means it's either genuinely active with recent tuition work or it's a stale record from the previous ecosystem. The old cron that reported QLHV ecosystem has been running for 3+ hours, but this group session only shows 13 minutes, which suggests it might be a separate live session rather than just a data artifact.\n\nI need to verify the current state since I already stopped the QLHV group yesterday. The cron timestamps are unreliable (showing 25-27 hours is unrealistic), so I should focus on what the session list actually shows right now rather than trusting the reported ages.","thinkingSignature":"fd7095dc46fca6d8aa2a770d7e87569ca2fd85dc69172b3f9a6b6d29d3e0a433"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t9g1ch6629ju_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["group"],"limit":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":273,"output":314,"cacheRead":7778,"cacheWrite":135882,"totalTokens":144247,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776166694976,"responseId":"062d5a2833ba23df6c7db00349e5472