{"type":"message","id":"7014caa7","parentId":"738e5874","timestamp":"2026-04-14T17:30:36.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead direct session was \"DEGRADED\" but the Agent Status cron reports it as the source of the message. The \"DEGRADED\" alert is coming from the cron itself. But the key issue is: is there actually a problem?\n\n1. cron:e7885813 (Agent Status) — 2 consecutive aborts, delivery stopped → this is the cron reporting its own issues\n2. cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV) — completed normally\n3. Pipeline DEGRADED due to Agent Status cron\n\nBut I'm the master-orchestrator running in a live session. The cron is reporting stale data about itself. \n\nLooking at the sessions list, both the QLHV and DTLX 5p monitors are still running and healthy, while the Agent Status cron just fired successfully with its own alert. The real question is whether that degraded status is still current or if it was a temporary issue that's already resolved.","thinkingSignature":"5ba0dac1008b406896b6eebec13e165ec9eefd9e8d15a2b5072cca69f4bf1432"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gjj4fkyzk1qr_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":10,"activeMinutes":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":300,"output":237,"cacheRead":7778,"cacheWrite":145828,"totalTokens":154143,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776187821532,"responseId":"062dacb08e00cb4fe4da0ff36466773a"}}
